description: This file defines external API function prototypes related to the Access Key Object in the ANSC (Advanced Networking Service Container) framework, including creation, removal, enrollment, and initialization functions.

methods.name: AnscCreateAccessKey
methods.description: Creates a new Access Key object, taking container, owner, and reserved handles as parameters.

methods.name: AnscAkoCreate
methods.description: Creates a new instance of the Access Key Object with given container, owner, and reserved handles.

methods.name: AnscAkoRemove
methods.description: Removes an existing Access Key Object identified by its handle.

methods.name: AnscAkoEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls or registers necessary objects for the Access Key Object.
